<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ861231-0121 </DOCNO><HL> Kroy Inc. Buyout Is Completed</HL><DD> 12/31/86</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM) </IN><DATELINE> SCOTTSDALE, Ariz.  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Kroy Inc. said an investor group led by the company's managers completed a leveraged buyout of the maker of printed lettering systems for $11.50 a share, or about $67.3 million.    As previously reported, Kroy said the investor group includes Donald W. Gustafson, Kroy's chairman; Errol W. Bartine, president and chief executive officer; and six other company executives.    Kroy said shareholders approved the acquisition at a special meeting earlier this month.    In a leveraged buyout, a company is acquired largely with borrowed money that is repaid with funds generated by the company's operations or through asset sales. </TEXT></DOC>